The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Bengal | IAS centre
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   IAS centre
                            
	Calcutta, July 17: An institute is planned to groom candidates for the IAS, Buddhadeb Bhattacharjee said today.         
	The institute will motivate and coach young boys and girls for the central civil services, he told the Assembly. The move is aimed at ensuring that Bengal produces more such officers.                                                                                                                                                                         
